// CI gate: verify issued certificates include tenantId in SAN
function validateCert(certPem, tenantId) {
  const cert = new X509.Cert(certPem);
  const sans = cert.getSubjectAltName();
  return sans.includes(`tenantId:${tenantId}`);
}

// Validate certificate chain integrity
function validateChain(chainPem) {
  const chain = X509.CertChain.fromPEM(chainPem);
  return chain.verify();
}
```

The code above demonstrates CI-level validation: the first function ensures each certificate contains the tenant identifier in its Subject Alternative Names, enabling tenant-aware access control. The second function verifies the entire certificate chain signature integrity before deployment, preventing compromised or tampered certificates from entering the production mesh.

