Set up real-time guardrails: trigger on export anomalies via Cloud Audit Logs (BigQuery dataExport jobs) using Cloud Logging sinks to Pub/Sub; automatically apply IAM Conditions with time-based restrictions (`request.time < timestamp('2024-01-01T00:00:00Z')`) and resource-based constraints (`resource.name.startsWith('projects/partner-project/datasets/')`) to temporarily restrict the partner destination; rotate the partner SA keys in Cloud KMS and disable old keys via Cloud Identity; reconfigure PSC endpoints to block the partner's project IP ranges; enable VPC Service Controls with service perimeters around BigQuery and restrict egress to the partner project; apply CMEK with key rotation and DLP data masking with de-identification templates; establish rollback using Cloud Deployment Manager templates and validate with synthetic data test exports.

```javascript
// Cloud Function triggered by audit log anomaly
exports.containExportAnomaly = async (event, context) => {
  const payload = JSON.parse(Buffer.from(event.data, 'base64').toString());
  const { protoPayload, resourceName } = payload;

  // Detect anomalous export patterns
  if (protoPayload.methodName === 'google.cloud.bigquery.v2.JobService.InsertJob' &&
      protoPayload.resourceName.includes('dataExport')) {

    // Apply temporary IAM Conditions
    await applyIAMConditions(resourceName, {
      title: 'Export Restriction',
      expression: `request.time < timestamp("${new Date(Date.now() + 3600000).toISOString()}") && !resource.name.startsWith("projects/partner-project/")`
    });

    // Rotate service account keys
    await rotateServiceAccountKeys('partner-service-account@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com');

    // Update PSC configuration
    await updatePSCConfig('partner-endpoint', { blocked: true });

    // Apply CMEK and DLP
    await applyCMKEDLP(resourceName);
  }
};
```

